@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title Activity - wlms/ManagedInstance
skinparam activity {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  diamondBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  diamondBorderColor #1d4ed8
  diamondFontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
  barColor #1d4ed8
}
start
partition "Observe and Bind" {
:Start from shared flow\nshared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg;
:Read desired ManagedInstance spec, tracked\nstatus, and delete intent;
if ("Tracked or explicit OCI identity present?") then (yes)
:Get the current OCI resource via\nGetManagedInstance;
else (no)
:Resolve an existing OCI resource through\nListManagedInstances using filters\ncompartmentId, displayName, id, pluginStatus;
:Persist the resolved or created OCI identity\ninto status;
endif
}
if ("Delete requested?") then (yes)
partition "Delete" {
:Delete path is not represented by imported\nprovider facts;
:Confirm deletion via GetManagedInstance or\nListManagedInstances until OCI reaches\nLOCAL_DELETE;
:Allow best-effort completion without finalizer\nretention;
}
stop
else (no)
partition "Lifecycle Classification" {
if ("OCI state is outside success targets?") then (yes)
:Return an unsuccessful reconcile result until\nOCI reaches ACTIVE, INACTIVE;
stop
endif
}
partition "Ready and Drift Handling" {
:Compare live OCI state against the\nrepo-authored mutation surface;
if ("Force-new or conflicting drift detected?") then (yes)
:Reject drift before OCI mutation for force-new\nfields compartmentId, displayName, id,\npluginStatus;
stop
endif
if ("Supported mutable drift detected?") then (yes)
:Apply UpdateManagedInstance only for mutable\nfields configuration;
else (no)
:Skip the no-op mutation path;
endif
:Run provider helper hooks\nupdate=tfresource.UpdateResource when the\nmatching field-driven path executes;
:Apply explicit follow-up semantics\ncreate=none; update=next reconcile\nGetManagedInstance confirmation; delete=none;
:Return success for the ACTIVE, INACTIVE\nsuccess state;
:Project required status and finalizer policy\nnone;
:Requeue on updating;
}
endif
stop
note right
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg
Start from the shared reconcile activity and
specialize provider-backed CRUD, wait, and
status-projection details here.
Controller-local activity diagrams add
list-lookup hints, secret policies, delete
handling, and open formal gaps.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers specialize the shared reconcile path
with formal runtime ownership.
service: wlms
slug: managedinstance
kind: ManagedInstance
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required / none
requeue: updating
provider states: create none; update none;
delete none
follow-up: create=none; update=next reconcile
GetManagedInstance confirmation; delete=none
supported drift: configuration
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartmentId, displayName, id, pluginStatus
create-only fields: none
list lookup: oci_wlms_managed_instances filters
compartmentId, displayName, id, pluginStatus;
exact id or exact compartmentId plus displayName
plus optional pluginStatus unique match;
duplicate matches fail
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
WLMS does not expose CreateManagedInstance or
DeleteManagedInstance in v65.110.0, so the
published runtime is bind/manage-existing only.
Successful UpdateManagedInstance responses
already return a ManagedInstance body. The
runtime uses that body plus one bounded
GetManagedInstance confirmation pass on the next
reconcile instead of inventing lifecycle or
work-request polling.
Delete is Kubernetes-local unbind only because
the SDK exposes no delete helper and no
cloud-side delete lifecycle for this family.
Plugin status remains a projected observed-state
field and optional bind filter, not a
controller-owned async lifecycle.
end note
@enduml
